Despite the past severe winter,damage to rapeseed acreage in Poland appears to be minor, theU.S. Agriculture Department's Counselor in Warsaw said in afield report.    The report, dated June 11, said official statements showthat about 40,000 hectares, less than 10 pct of sown area, wasplowed under this year compared with the usual 15 pct.    Rapeseed production is forecast at 1.1 mln tonnes, 200,000tonnes below the record crop produced in 1986, but 35 pct aboveprevious forecasts, the report said. Reuter&#3;